================================================================================
IMPORTANT NOTES
================================================================================

⚠️  CRITICAL:
   - ALWAYS restrict allowed_ssh_cidr to your IP only
   - Never commit terraform.tfvars to git (contains secrets)
   - Backup your kubeconfig after deployment
   - Save the rke2_token output for node additions

⚠️  DEPLOYMENT:
   - First control plane node must be ready before workers join
   - RKE2 installation takes 3-5 minutes per node
   - HCCM and CSI deployment takes additional 2-3 minutes
   - Load balancer health checks may show unhealthy initially

⚠️  COSTS:
   - Control plane: cpx21 × 3 = ~€30/month
   - Workers: cpx31 × 2 = ~€40/month
   - Load balancer: lb11 = ~€5/month
   - Volumes: ~€0.04/GB/month
   - Network traffic: First 20TB free, then €1/TB

⚠️  LIMITATIONS:
   - Hetzner CCM v1.30.0+ required after July 2026
   - CSI volumes are ReadWriteOnce only
   - Network zone must match server locations
   - Maximum 100 resources per network

================================================================================
QUICK REFERENCE COMMANDS
================================================================================

# Deployment
terraform init
terraform plan -out=tfplan
terraform apply tfplan

# Access Cluster
export KUBECONFIG=$(pwd)/kubeconfig.yaml
kubectl get nodes -o wide
kubectl get pods -n kube-system

# SSH Access
ssh -i ~/.ssh/id_ed25519 root@<CP_IP>

# Check Logs
journalctl -u rke2-server -f  # Control plane
journalctl -u rke2-agent -f   # Workers

# Get Token (sensitive)
terraform output -raw rke2_token

# Destroy Everything
terraform destroy

